The paper deals with capacity regions and bounds for interference channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of entropy and coding techniques suggests a possible connection to statistical learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) as well. Finally, the paper introduces a new upper bound on the capacity region, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of signal processing (cs.SI).
